reopening_plan:
MVA Covid-19  Policies, Procedures and Protocols School Year 2020-2021
Marble Valley Academy has reviewed and taken into consideration the guidance from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to determine, in close consultation with El Dorado County health authorities, what actions to take to further reduce the potential risk of coronavirus transmission in our school community. 

General MVA Community Safety Guidelines 

Campus/Class Safety Measures
Although masks are not mandatory, they will be readily available to students, teachers, staff, and visitors.  Teachers will be wearing masks in the classroom settings where applicable. Families may request student desk shields for further protection. 
Other Standard Protocols:
Hand sanitizer stations will be available throughout the school 
Class social distancing will be practiced
Classes will visit hand washing stations before and after lunch, and throughout the day
Clean AND disinfect frequently touched surfaces daily. This includes tables, doorknobs, light switches, countertops, handles, desks, phones, keyboards, toilets, faucets, and sinks
Class separation will be required for all assemblies and large multi-purpose functions
Small Group Gatherings will be encouraged on the playground and during break and lunch but not with other classes if possible

Classroom Covid19 Safety Protocols
Computer lab - Cleaning Policy Rubbing Alcohol, UV Light, Keyboard covers, bleach legos.
Students will use their assigned computer air book from cart only to minimize risk
Students will be asked to not share books, pencils or any personal supplies.
Students will be asked to leave all personal belongings in their personal dedicated locker or hook outside of the classroom to reduce risk and exposure.
Students will be asked to NOT ARRIVE on campus until 8:10-8:30
Jr. High (and S8th) Students will enter the Quad area door, all other students will enter gym door and go straight to the classroom for temperature taking, and other COVID measures.

Teacher Protocols
Teachers will open their classroom at 8:10 am
Teachers will do the following 3 steps before admitting into classroom
Confirm no temperature with handheld thermometer
Confirm a hand washing at door or before
Confirm no COVID exposure
Confirm all personal items have been left OUTSIDE classroom in locker/hooks

Parent/guardian Interactions Safety Protocols
Parents(or those dropping and picking up their children on a daily basis) should refrain from coming into the school setting if possible.
Parents will not be allowed to bring lunches or forgotten supplies on campus to their student’s class rooms, but must drop these items at the front desk for delivery.
All surrounding side doors will be shut and locked during school hours, so any communication must occur thru the front office door
Any student who has a family member who has tested positive for COVID, will be asked to self quarantine for 10-14 days.
Parents are asked to keep any child home with any sign of flu symptoms until the child is health and well.


MVA Exposure Control Plan
Protocol for a positive Test for COVID19 for a MVA  teacher / staff / student

Safety Measures & Protocols
Families will be notified when a student, teacher or school administrator has tested positive
A quarantine teacher will come on campus as a substitute for the Covid19 positive teacher
Separate learning environment after exposure for the students or option to stay home for a quarantine period with alternative temporary education options
Positive Student / Teacher / Staff member will be asked to quarantine for 10-14 days 
Student/Teacher/Staff will be asked to NOT return without a negative test result. 


Please see Communicable disease control policies and procedures for further answers. School officials are encouraged to consult with local and state health department officials regarding communicable disease control measures if and when there is a positive test result. Marble Valley Administration will continue to monitor recommendations.

reopening_plan:
Our superintendent will update or COVID-19 Safety Plan on Thursday, 1/28/21, but our current plan is on our school website: www.stannesporterville.org

https://a18749b7-51f8-4d94-a50c-2995a3f69097.filesusr.com/ugd/854243_f16f1e141c574f5798f4b4c5750bf746.pdf

Presently, the school is teaching virtually.  St. Alphonsus School schedule starts at 8:00 AM to 3:00 PM Monday to Thursday and 8:00 AM to 12:00 PM on Friday.  Fridays are Faculty collaboration from 1:00 PM to 3:30 PM .   Every teacher has group sessions after lunch to meet with student in smaller groups or one to one. If packets need to be given to students they are either scanned and emailed or a pick up day and time are scheduled.
Posted at the school main entrance is the school's safety plan and school maps.  A check-in table with sign in questionnaire and temperature check  is immediately upon entering the school.  Covid-19 signage is throughout the school halls, offices and classrooms.  An isolation room is on the first floor with necessary PPE and signage and easy exit path when leaving the school.   Office, faculty and staff, and school parents received the safety plan with school maps as posted outdoors in the entry of the school.
When it is safe to return we expect to apply for a waiver for grades Transitional Kinder to 2nd Grade.   School routines are designed for safety protocol and follow the CDC and Health Department guidelines.  PPE is available for students not in possession of masks.  Classes can be outdoors with safety measures or indoors with spacing.  All classrooms are sanitized based on a custodial schedule and teachers maintain sanitation practices during the day.   Frequently touched areas are sanitized regularly.

reopening_plan:
Date: May 11 th, 2020
TO: All Parents
REF: New Safety Guidelines for Parents and Children
At our school, health, safety and the welfare of all the staff and children in our care are our number one priority. With the present condition of COVID-19 (Coronavirus Disease), we are very concerned about the safety of everyone who enters our school, including parents and anyone authorized to pick up your child. Recognizing this, we have introduced the attached safety protocol.
Please review and follow these guidelines diligently. Your patience and cooperation are necessary to ensure the health and safety of everyone. If you have any questions and concerns, please call or email us right away.
Thank you
OC Montessori Academy
NEW SAFETY GUIDELINES FOR ALL PARENTS AND CHILDREN
Effective: May 18 th, 2020
1.	If you, your child or anyone in your household had fever, cough, difficulty breathing, any other signs of illness in the past 24 hours, or had exposure to another individual with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 cases, PLEASE DO NOT ENTER THE SCHOOL and call us right away.
2.	Face Mask is required for all adults exiting their vehicles. If your child has a face mask, please encourage them to wear it, but we cannot force them to do it.
3.	to leave the premise if we A staff member will be waiting at the gate for your child to enter. Please wait outside the gate on the markings to allow 6 ft distance. If you would like to talk to Ms. Karen, please wait outside the gate as well.
PARENTS ARE NO LONGER ALLOWED INSIDE THE GATE OR BUILDING.  Drop Off, We will have your child's temperature checked (children with a 100.0 and up cannot stay). Once your child is allowed inside the gate please sign your child IN.
** During Pick Up, please stop at the front gate. The Director or a teacher will help you get your child from his/her classroom. Please DO NOT open the gate.
4.	Please note that it is still mandatory to sign your child in and out every day, and YOU MUST USE YOUR OWN PEN. So, please make sure to keep one with you at all times. Any missing signature found can still be fined by State Licensing.
5.	Every student must bring his/her own lunch in a lunch pail with snacks and lunch (put an ice pack to keep food cold and use thermos to keep food warm, personal utensils, and water bottle. The school will temporarily stop providing school lunches until further notice. The staff will not be able to heat lunches. All lunch pails must be placed on the cart outside and the water bottles on the labeled trays. EVERYTHING THAT BELONGS TO YOUR CHILD MUST HAVE HIS/HER NAME CLEARLY MARKED. MANY LUNCH PAILS AND WATER BOTTLES ARE IDENTICAL.
6.	Please do not stay longer than necessary to drop off or pick up your child. All parents must stay 6 feet away from each other while at school. You will be asked feel that you are not following these safety protocols.
7.	Please know that all staff are also required to have their temperature checked daily, wear masks at school, and wash hands before entering the building and regularly throughout the day.
8.	All payment should be in personal check or
9.	Any questions or concerns, please call or email us. oc@ppsnschs.com
NEW CLASSROOM AND OUTDOOR PLAY CHANGES
I. All class sizes are now reduced to a maximum of 10 students per teacher.
2.	Class groups will rotate indoor/outdoor/snack and lunch areas/restroom use.
3.	The restroom in Rooms 1 and 2 will be used by a maximum of 3 students a time (using every other toilet) for distancing purposes. Room 3 and 4 bathroom will be used by a maximum or 2 students at a time. The flush handles and toilet seats are wiped down after each use.
4.	Longer classes will be held outdoors.
5.	Most doors will remain open throughout the day for continuous ventilation.
6.	All tables and toys are now separated (with as much distance as the classroom space permits) to allow students to practice social distancing. The tables and toys (kept at smaller quantities) will be sanitized immediately after each use. Montessori rugs will not be used.
7.	Children will be sitting by their tables for circle time.
8.	Absolutely no toys from home will be allowed on Share Day (Show and Tell). Teachers will use creative ways such as drawing a picture, show and tell their friends what they drew and why.
9.	Before nap, the teachers will check all students' temperature again. Anyone with suspected symptoms or a temperature of 100.0 and up will be isolated, parents called to have their child picked up right away—not at the end of the parents' workday.
10.	At nap time, each mat will be spread out to allow as much distance between these as the classroom space permits. In addition, the head of each bed will be arranged alternately, in opposite directions to add more space between each child's face.
11.	Napping students will continue to take their sheets home every Friday. These must be washed and brought back every Monday. We encourage you to keep a second set of sheets at school in case you forget. Unfortunately, school sheets will not be available as staff cannot take them home to wash nor can we allow these sheets to go home. Therefore, if you forget, and you do not have a second set of sheets at school, you will be called to pick up your child before nap time. For the health and safety of everyone, we will not be making any exceptions.
12.	Small outdoor toys will be removed to discourage multiple user at the same time.. Bike handles will be sanitized after each use.
13.	Reading Books will not be sent home. These will remain at school for daily use.
14.	There will not be homework assignments until Fall semester. Any changes to the current homework system will be announced when the new school year begins.
15.	Every child must keep a set of changing clothes (Room 1 should have at least 2 sets), in a labeled Ziplock bag, and a labeled light jacket at school at all times.
16.	Unnecessary bags or backpacks will no longer be allowed. Only lunch pails and water bottles are permitted to be brought back and forth from home every day.
17.	Children should not carry Hand Sanitizers with them. They will play, share and possibly ingest these. They will be asked to wash their hands very often!
